[SN]TITLE[SN]
£2.25m for universities to lead health research

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A national centre aimed at improving health and wellbeing is to be established with the help of £2.25m funding.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Universities in Bangor, Swansea and Cardiff will lead research into areas like physical activity, arthritis, asthma, infection and injuries.
Aims will include giving children a healthy start and adding more quality years to people's lives.
It is being funded by Welsh government body Health and Care Research Wales.
